The National Universities Commission (NUC) has granted full accreditation to five undergraduate academic programmes in Ladoke Akintola University of Technology (LAUTECH), Ogbomoso, for a period of five years. The NUC, in a letter signed on behalf of the Executive Secretary by Director of Accreditation, Dr. Maryam Sali, listed the programmes to include Fine and Applied Arts, Agricultural Engineering, Chemical Engineering as well as Pure and Applied Physics and Statistics. The letter stated that the accreditation (which is not new) was consequent upon the one carried out in LAUTECH between October and November 2021. 